{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}
{% set nav = 'home' %}

{% block title %}Robinson Huron Treaty · A member resource for the treaty and its 21 nations{% endblock %}
{% block description %}A member-led resource for the Robinson Huron Treaty and its 21 First Nations: what the 1850 treaty is, the communities of the territory, what is happening on the land, and the member-led transparency work on the shared settlement.{% endblock %}
{% block og_description %}A member-led resource for the Robinson Huron Treaty and its 21 First Nations: the treaty, the communities, the land, and the transparency work on the shared settlement.{% endblock %}

{% block head_styles %}
<style>
  /* TEMPORARY live-meeting banner (remove with the banner markup below once
     the July 23, 2026 meeting has concluded and /live points at the recording). */
  .live-strip { display: block; background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--indigo-deep), var(--magenta)); color: #fff; text-decoration: none; padding: 12px 0; }
  .live-strip .wrap { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .live-strip__dot { flex: none; width: 10px; height: 10px; border-radius: 50%; background: #fff; box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6); animation: live-pulse 1.6s ease-out infinite; }
  @keyframes live-pulse { to { box-shadow: 0 0 0 9px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0); } }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) { .live-strip__dot { animation: none; } }
  .live-strip strong { font-weight: 700; color: #fff; }
  .live-strip__go { margin-left: auto; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: underline; white-space: nowrap; }
  .live-strip:hover .live-strip__go { text-decoration: none; }
</style>
{% endblock %}

{% block hero %}
{# TEMPORARY: July 23, 2026 members' meeting stream. Remove this banner (and
   its styles in head_styles above) after the meeting; /live stays up for the
   recording. #}
<a class="live-strip" href="/live">
  <span class="wrap wrap--wide">
    <span class="live-strip__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
    <span><strong>Today, July 23:</strong> the Sagamok members' meeting is being streamed live by a member.</span>
    <span class="live-strip__go">Watch the stream</span>
  </span>
</a>
<section class="hero">
  <div class="wrap wrap--wide">
    <p class="eyebrow">A resource for the treaty and its 21 nations</p>
    <h1>The Robinson Huron Treaty, in one place.</h1>
    <p class="lead">The Robinson Huron Treaty is more than the settlement. It is a living relationship to the land, its resources, and the 21 First Nations of the territory. This is a member-led resource for anyone in or asking about the treaty: what it is, who the communities are, what is happening on the land, and how members are working together on transparency.</p>
    <form id="rht-ask-hero" class="hero-ask" role="search">
      <label class="hero-ask__label" for="rht-ask-hero-input">Aanii. Ask a question to get started</label>
      <div class="hero-ask__row">
        <input id="rht-ask-hero-input" type="text" autocomplete="off" maxlength="500" placeholder="What is the settlement? Mental health help near me? Find my nation.">
        <button type="submit">Ask</button>
      </div>
      <p class="hero-ask__note">Plain, cited answers from this hub's pages. A community resource, not the Nation or the Fund.</p>
    </form>
  </div>
</section>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <h2>Start here</h2>
  <ul class="community-grid">
    <li><a class="community-card" href="/treaty">
      <p class="name">The Treaty</p>
      <p class="pillar-desc">What the 1850 treaty is, the $4 annuity, the 2023 settlement, and the 2024 Supreme Court decision, in plain language.</p>
    </a></li>
    <li><a class="community-card" href="/communities">
      <p class="name">Communities</p>
      <p class="pillar-desc">The 21 signatory First Nations of the territory, one page each, grouped by region.</p>
    </a></li>
    <li><a class="community-card" href="/land">
      <p class="name">The Land</p>
      <p class="pillar-desc">Decisions on the territory: energy and resource projects, the environment, and member wellbeing.</p>
    </a></li>
    <li><a class="community-card" href="/standard">
      <p class="name">Transparency</p>
      <p class="pillar-desc">The member-led work on the shared settlement: the standard any member can use, and the treaty-wide ask.</p>
    </a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The member-led Circle</h2>
  <p>Inside this resource is the member-led Circle: members and beneficiaries from across the treaty, asking clear, respectful questions together about how our shared settlement is governed. The Circle is one part of the hub, the part where members organize and act. Everything else here, the treaty orientation, the community pages, and the land section, is open to anyone.</p>

  <div class="btn-row">
    <a class="btn" href="/circle">Meet the Circle</a>
    <a class="btn btn--alt" href="/treaty">Start with the treaty</a>
  </div>
{% endblock %}
